name: EA-012-Sartre
description:
Jean-Paul Sartre (1905 - 1980 aC) was a French philosopher, writer and critic, known as a representative of existentialism. He believed that intellectuals have to play an active role in society. He was a militant artist, and supported left-wing political causes with his life and work.

Digital Watercolor Vector Illustration made in Adobe Photoshop, 1200x1200px, 200dpi, JPEG, 2021
